data.description: Welcome home! One of a kind amazing ranch style living on 5 acres in Cache! Nestled in a secluded spot next to prestigious Wildflower Estates (but not in a subdivision so there are no deed restrictions!), this custom built beauty features over 2100 sf with 4 bedrooms, 2.5 bathrooms, 2 car garage, a workshop/barn and Connex, plus 3 sheds/lean-to's all with electric, fenced pasture and a huge covered back patio that overlooks the backyard with a definite highlight: Your very own creek! Wow! The seller spared no expense in remodeling this already amazing home. The interior impresses with a functional floor plan that flows nicely from the foyer into the 2nd living area that could be a formal dining, great room, play room etc into a well appointed kitchen (2 pantries, stainless and black appliances with a refrigerator that stays) with breakfast bar to accommodate bar stools for casual meals and opens to the den with floor-to-ceiling brick fireplace and a stove insert to keep you warm on a cold winter’s day. French doors with blinds between the panes are a breeze to clean and lead to a large country back porch that is perfect for family BBQs or large scale entertaining. Inside, a hallway with built-in designer shelving leads to the west north wing of the property that sports 4 good size bedrooms, a hall bath with a soaker tub, a half bath for guests, a utility room with a washer and dryer set that stays, and a large primary bedroom with a matching boudoir vanity, two closets (one is a walk-in), and an ensuite bath featuring oil rubbed bronze hardware and walk-in shower. Wow! The floor coverings throughout are wood effect Pergo floors in kitchen, den and hallway, tile in baths and utility room and carpet in the bedrooms. Outside, this 5 acre property offers an in-ground storm shelter to keep your family safe during inclement Oklahoma weather, RV parking in the yard, a near new HVAC system that is top-of-the-line with radiant ceiling heat and multiple thermostats for zoned control and a warranty (7 years left with Alltech), the septic system is environmentally friendly, the riding mower (can stay with the right offer) will keep the yard looking sharp and the near new roof (2 yrs young) will save a bundle on insurance. Imagine! You could live off the land: keep and raise chickens, horses, cows, sheep, goats etc and harvest your new private orchard (fruit and pecan trees bear every year) to make you self-sustaining. The possibilities are endless! Perfectly located in the award winning Cache school district (bus pickup by driveway), within a 10-15 min drive radius to Fort Sill, shopping and dining at the new shopping center with Target, TJ Maxx and Academy Sports or participate in the active lifestyle in nearby Medicine Park with Festivals, shopping, dining and sightseeing, the Wichita Mountain Wildlife Refuge with hiking trails and Lake Lawtonka with fishing, boating and swimming. This is the hard to find lifestyle that offers relaxing or entertaining on your back porch watching your horses graze and/or your kiddos frolic  or the tree swings and/or explore the creek. It truly doesn’t get any better than this! Due to proximity of the creek, property may require flood insurance with certain loans and lenders. Please call or text Stefanie Johnson at 580 583 5238 for more information or to schedule a showing.
